Heidelberg police have opened an inquest docket after a human skull, backbone and some bones were found scattered in the veld in Spaarwater Plots yesterday. Police spokesperson, Capt Thivhulawi Tshilate said: “That a plot resident or owner was walking his dog in the open veld when one of them discovered the human skull and other bones. The dog owner immediately reported it to the police.” The police are now appealing to anyone whose family or relative went missing a few months ago to visit Heidelberg police detectives to assist with investigations. Meanwhile, police in Olievenhoutbosch are investigating a case of assault with intent to commit grievous bodily harm after a taxi owner allegedly attacked his employee with an axe on Monday. The taxi owner is reportedly in hiding. The taxi driver supposedly didn’t declare a long-distance trip. The victim sustained multiple injuries and was taken to Kalafong Hospital. -DIKELEDI MOLOBELA